# Local Environment

## Package Manager

- **pnpm** is installed via Homebrew (`brew install pnpm`), available at `/opt/homebrew/bin/pnpm`
- The shell also has an Aikido security wrapper (`aikido-pnpm`) that intercepts `pnpm` as a shell function. Direct binary lookup may resolve the wrapper, not the Homebrew binary.
- The repo declares `"packageManager": "pnpm@10.29.3"` in `package.json`.

## Build Tool

- **Turborepo** (`turbo`) is installed globally via npm (`npm install -g turbo`), available at `/opt/homebrew/bin/turbo`
- A local `turbo` is also installed as a devDependency (v2.7.4) via `pnpm install`
- `pnpm build` delegates to `turbo run build`

## Installing Dependencies

- Run `pnpm install` from the repo root — this installs all 2,246 packages across 39 workspace projects
- Requires unrestricted permissions (no sandbox) to actually write to `node_modules`
- Some native build scripts are ignored by default (esbuild, sharp, etc.) — run `pnpm approve-builds` if needed

## Building

- Run `pnpm build` from the repo root to build all packages and examples via Turborepo
- Build order is managed by Turborepo based on `dependsOn: ["^build"]` in `turbo.json`
- The MCP example (`examples/mcp`) needs a successful build to produce `dist/index.html`, which the MCP server loads at startup

## Dev Servers

- All dev servers use [portless](https://github.com/vercel-labs/portless) for automatic port assignment via `.localhost:1355` URLs
- `portless` must be installed globally (not as a project dependency)
- Run `pnpm dev` from the root to start all dev servers via Turborepo
